==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encasement
<hw>En*case"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Casement</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of encasing; also,
that which encases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>An old theory of generation
similar to embo⟦icir⟧tement. See <er>Ovulist</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encash</ent>⟦br⟧
